%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprofessionals%20early%20in%20their%20careers%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20employers%20expect%20them%20to%20%26quot%3Bintrinsically%20know%20how%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20make%20your%20role%20more%20productive%20and%20more%20efficient.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20often%20without%20employers%20providing%20training%20and%20support%20on%20how%20workers%20should%20use%20AI%20to%20level%20up%20the%20quality%20of%20their%20work%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a0a0b121-44d4-4d9b-81a5-56bccc56fb77%5C%22%3ECompetition%20for%20roles%20is%20up%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERegardless%20of%20workers'%20experience%20levels%2C%20employers%20are%20ratcheting%20up%20their%20expectations%20for%20roles%20because%20they%20can.%20In%20many%20fields%2C%20there's%20a%20deep%20supply%20of%20knowledgeable%20workers%2C%20and%20a%20sizable%20share%20of%20candidates%20now%20bring%20advanced%20degrees%2C%20Spencer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEmployers%20are%20just%20seeing%20sort%20of%20the%20baseline%20qualifications%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20bringing%20to%20the%20table%20and%20then%20raising%20their%20own%20qualifications%20accordingly%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20comes%20as%20workers%2C%20broadly%2C%20are%20staying%20on%20the%20job%20for%20less%20time%20than%20years%20ago.%20By%20the%20start%20of%202024%2C%20US%20workers%20had%20been%20with%20their%20employer%20an%20average%20of%203.9%20years%2C%20the%20lowest%20number%20since%202002%2C%20according%20to%20a%20biennial%20snapshot%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fpdf%2Ftenure.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELabor%20Department%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20in%20healthcare%20or%20in%20a%20high-demand%20area%20like%20AI%2C%20you%20might%20be%20all%20set%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20career%20security.%20For%20many%20desk%20workers%2C%20however%2C%20the%20job%20market%20can%20look%20far%20less%20reassuring.%3C%2Fp%